sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a persistent disk in the specified project.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Zone - Name of the zone.
  • Name - Name of the resource.
  • Type - Disk type resource describing which disk type to use to create the disk.
  • Description - Description of this resource.
  • Size GB - Size of the persistent disk, specified in GB.
  • Source Image - Source image used to create this disk.
  • Source Snapshot - Source snapshot used to create this disk.
  • Physical Block Size Bytes - Physical block size of the persistent disk, in bytes.
  • Guest OS Features - A list of features to enable on the guest operating system.
  • Labels - Labels an object containing Key and Value.

Outputs:

  • Disk - Disk an object containing Name, Zone, Target Link, User, Insert Time, Start Time, Self-Link, ID, Status.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Persistent Disk , Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID has been passed.
  • Requested disk name is already created.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Persistent Disk connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Persistent Disk Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

sys_hub_action_type_snapshot.description:
Creates a persistent disk in the specified project.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Zone - Name of the zone.
  • Name - Name of the resource.
  • Type - Disk type resource describing which disk type to use to create the disk.
  • Description - Description of this resource.
  • Size GB - Size of the persistent disk, specified in GB.
  • Source Image - Source image used to create this disk.
  • Source Snapshot - Source snapshot used to create this disk.
  • Physical Block Size Bytes - Physical block size of the persistent disk, in bytes.
  • Guest OS Features - A list of features to enable on the guest operating system.
  • Labels - Labels an object containing Key and Value.

Outputs:

  • Disk - Disk an object containing Name, Zone, Target Link, User, Insert Time, Start Time, Self-Link, ID, Status.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Persistent Disk , Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID has been passed.
  • Requested disk name is already created.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Persistent Disk connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Persistent Disk Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
